<bug>
	<id>96645</id>
	<title>LibreOffice website should provide 64-bit build download link directly for 64-bit device</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Hello everyone,</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I have heard LibreOffice is providing native x86-64 Windows build now, but the download page is still provide x86 build directly despite the user is using x64 build web browser.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Mozilla Firefox announced version 43.0 is offered to Release channel users on December 15, 2015.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">Since then, a native, 64-bit Windows build is also available on their download page, so they also support x64 devides on both Linux and Windows platforms.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">To distinct different hardware structure, Firefox is using different strings in the user agent.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.4">Such as:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win32; x86; rv:43.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/43.0
Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64; rv:43.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/43.0</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">In this case you have an entry of providing download link for x86/x64 build automatically.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">So plaese provide 64-bit build download directly.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
